Package: ubuntu-zombie
Version: __VERSION__
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: bash (>= 4), coreutils, sudo, ca-certificates, curl
Recommends: openssh-server, ufw, fail2ban, unattended-upgrades, jq
Maintainer: Japer Technology <ops@japer.technology>
Homepage: https://github.com/japer-technology/ubuntu-zombie
Description: Resident AI Systems Administrator for Ubuntu Desktop LTS
 Ubuntu Zombie adds a private, root-capable AI Systems Administrator
 account to supported Ubuntu Desktop LTS machines so an owner can ask
 the machine to diagnose, explain, configure, repair, and operate
 itself.
 .
 This package only stages the installer, payload, and documentation
 under /usr/share/ubuntu-zombie/ and exposes a wrapper at
 /usr/sbin/ubuntu-zombie. The wrapper delegates to scripts/install.sh
 from the staged tree; nothing is changed on the host until the
 operator runs `sudo ubuntu-zombie install`.
 .
 See /usr/share/doc/ubuntu-zombie/README.md after install.
